It's not that serious.

708
01:02:36,293 --> 01:02:38,795
You've got the money.
You didn't kill the old lady.

709
01:02:38,922 --> 01:02:42,132
You're just there to plant doubt
in the minds of the police.

710
01:02:42,259 --> 01:02:44,427
They'll never charge you.

711
01:02:44,594 --> 01:02:46,762
You were supposed to get caught
tonight breaking in.

712
01:02:46,929 --> 01:02:50,056
They'd pull you in, ask you about the old lady,
and you wouldn't know anything.

713
01:02:50,182 --> 01:02:52,726
They could still have charged me
for breaking and entering.

714
01:02:52,853 --> 01:02:55,396
But you did break and enter.

715
01:02:55,521 --> 01:02:57,773
And for whatever reason,
you didn't get caught red-handed.

716
01:03:00,985 --> 01:03:03,862
He came in. He went down.

717
01:03:03,989 --> 01:03:07,824
I didn't hang around long enough
to find out whether he could get up.

718
01:03:07,951 --> 01:03:10,869
It's his blood on my hammer.

719
01:03:10,996 --> 01:03:14,289
How could you do this to me?

720
01:03:14,416 --> 01:03:16,876
It's nothing personal.

721
01:03:17,001 --> 01:03:19,545
When I began this,
I didn't even know you.

722
01:03:23,884 --> 01:03:26,552
[ Hammer Thuds On Floor ]

723
01:03:26,677 --> 01:03:29,221
- I'm going to the police in the morning.
- You can't.

724
01:03:30,599 --> 01:03:32,807
I'm going,
and I'm gonna tell them everything.

725
01:03:32,934 --> 01:03:34,810
You can't,
'cause they won't believe you.

726
01:03:34,936 --> 01:03:37,104
I'm gonna tell them everything.
They'll believe me because it's the truth.

727
01:03:37,230 --> 01:03:40,315
- Not if you haven't got someone
to back up your story.
- You could.

728
01:03:40,442 --> 01:03:42,943
I won't.

729
01:03:43,068 --> 01:03:46,529
They'll make you, because your lies
won't stand up to the truth.

730
01:03:52,161 --> 01:03:55,663
- I wouldn't do this if I were you.
- [ Door Shuts ]

731
01:04:00,753 --> 01:04:02,337
That's it.

732
01:04:04,257 --> 01:04:06,717
I mean, if you've got
any questions, then —

733
01:04:06,842 --> 01:04:09,385
One or two.

734
01:04:09,512 --> 01:04:12,472
You see, we don't actually have
any unsolved murders of old ladies...

735
01:04:12,599 --> 01:04:15,226
- at the present.
- You must have.

736
01:04:15,351 --> 01:04:19,562
There's no such ongoing investigation.

737
01:04:19,688 --> 01:04:22,190
And we don't know
this Mr. Cobb of yours.

738
01:04:24,277 --> 01:04:26,362
I warned you
he'd look in the envelope.

739
01:04:27,489 --> 01:04:29,532
He gave me his word.
I believed him.

740
01:04:29,657 --> 01:04:31,909
It's nothing personal.
He couldn't help it.

741
01:04:32,034 --> 01:04:34,036
I mean, he's a born peeper.

742
01:04:37,998 --> 01:04:40,875
Anyway, down to business.

743
01:04:41,001 --> 01:04:43,211
[ Scoffs ]
"Business"?

744
01:04:45,548 --> 01:04:47,215
[ Police Investigator ]
Perhaps there's...

745
01:04:47,342 --> 01:04:50,385
something else
you'd like to tell me, hmm?

746
01:04:51,512 --> 01:04:53,972
Anything.

747
01:04:56,016 --> 01:04:58,393
- Where's the hammer?
- It's in that bag.

748
01:05:00,981 --> 01:05:02,648
What are you gonna do with it?

749
01:05:04,693 --> 01:05:07,736
The old man was very specific
about how I should do things.

750
01:05:09,822 --> 01:05:11,864
What's the old man
got to say about it?

751
01:05:11,992 --> 01:05:15,160
Well, he is letting me keep
all the money from his safe.

752
01:05:16,413 --> 01:05:18,706
Anything at all.

753
01:05:18,831 --> 01:05:20,540
Your side of things.

754
01:05:23,168 --> 01:05:25,670
He says your demands
have become too unreasonable.

755
01:05:25,797 --> 01:05:28,090
You've become too greedy
in your blackmail.

756
01:05:28,257 --> 01:05:30,925
He said something
about you being a witness...

757
01:05:31,052 --> 01:05:33,429
to an incident
that happened in this very room.

758
01:05:33,597 --> 01:05:37,474
He was very precise about exactly
how and where I should take care of things.

759
01:05:37,601 --> 01:05:39,934
Something about
a bloodstained carpet...

760
01:05:40,103 --> 01:05:42,688
that you've got stashed away
to back up your story...

761
01:05:42,813 --> 01:05:44,940
should it ever be told.

762
01:05:46,025 --> 01:05:48,277
Did you talk to her?

763
01:05:48,402 --> 01:05:50,612
We found her this morning.

764
01:05:52,239 --> 01:05:53,281
[ Screaming ]

765
01:05:53,407 --> 01:05:54,991
What do you mean, "found her"?

766
01:05:55,117 --> 01:05:56,909
Her body.

767
01:05:57,954 --> 01:06:01,539
We also found a hammer
with two types of blood on it.

768
01:06:01,666 --> 01:06:05,336
One type I assume will match
the bloke you put in hospital.

769
01:06:06,463 --> 01:06:08,380
All her fingers were smashed.

770
01:06:08,505 --> 01:06:10,798
You must have tortured her
to get the combination.

771
01:06:10,925 --> 01:06:12,968
I didn't touch her!

772
01:06:14,219 --> 01:06:16,929
We also found
some interesting items in your flat...

773
01:06:17,056 --> 01:06:19,766
in this shoebox under your bed.

774
01:06:19,893 --> 01:06:24,021
Among various items reported missing
by the deceased last week, we found...

775
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:27,148
these pairs of ladies' underwear.

776
01:06:27,275 --> 01:06:29,193
Are they hers?

777
01:06:29,318 --> 01:06:32,362
I assume so,
since we found them stashed...

778
01:06:32,489 --> 01:06:35,324
with these passport-style
photographs of the deceased.

779
01:06:37,327 --> 01:06:40,621
We also found this pearl earring...

780
01:06:40,746 --> 01:06:43,164
which exactly matched...

781
01:06:43,333 --> 01:06:46,043
the one worn by the deceased
at the time of her death.

782
01:06:46,168 --> 01:06:48,711
- A little trophy?
- No.

783
01:06:48,838 --> 01:06:52,341
It was Cobb who planted it
when we turned over her place.

784
01:06:52,467 --> 01:06:55,135
Go and collar him.
I gave you his address.

785
01:06:56,762 --> 01:07:00,181
We checked the address you gave us.
There's no Cobb there.

786
01:07:00,307 --> 01:07:02,851
The flat belongs to a Mr....

787
01:07:04,603 --> 01:07:06,355
D. Lloyd.

788
01:07:07,606 --> 01:07:09,983
He's just returned from holiday...

789
01:07:10,110 --> 01:07:13,695
and he told us that while he was away,
his flat had been burgled.

790
01:07:13,822 --> 01:07:15,948
Not much was missing...

791
01:07:17,032 --> 01:07:19,492
but his new credit card
hasn't yet arrived.

792
01:07:19,619 --> 01:07:21,912
Well, that was Cobb.
We used it to...

793
01:07:22,038 --> 01:07:24,539
pay for a meal in a restaurant.

794
01:07:24,666 --> 01:07:27,042
We found this at your flat.

795
01:07:28,711 --> 01:07:30,670
It was Cobb...

796
01:07:31,715 --> 01:07:33,590
who stole it.

797
01:07:33,717 --> 01:07:35,925
Is that your handwriting?

798
01:07:38,762 --> 01:07:40,221
Yes.

